cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.RO

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper focuses on building detection in remote sensing images using CNN-based object detection methods. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed method utilizes CNN for feature extraction and bounding box regression, which falls under the domain of AI. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper presents an end-to-end model that is trained to predict orientation, location, and extent simultaneously, which is a machine learning task. 
4. cs.GR (Graphics): The paper proposes an algorithm to estimate the Intersection over Union (IoU) overlap between any two arbitrarily oriented boxes, which is related to graphics. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics): The proposed method can be applied to robotics applications such as autonomous navigation and mapping, which falls under the domain of robotics.
